            <title><![CDATA[IEEE VTS 杰出讲者Yonghui Li教师讲座通知]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[IEEE VTS 杰出讲者Yonghui Li教师讲座通知]]></description>
            <link>https://today.hit.edu.cn/article/2025/04/28/121321</link>
            <guid isPermaLink="true">https://today.hit.edu.cn/article/2025/04/28/121321</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 28 Apr 2025 15:12:47 GMT</pubDate>
            <content:encoded>&lt;p style=&quot;text-indent:21.0000pt; text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;应我校电信学院吴宣利教授、吴玮副教授的邀请，在&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;IEEE VTS哈尔滨分会IEEE ComSoc哈尔滨分会、IEEE BTS哈尔滨分会的支持下，无线通信领域的著名学者，IEEE VTS杰出讲师，悉尼大学Yonghui Li教授，将在线为我校师生进行学术讲座，讲座将重点讨论5G以及未来移动通信中超高可靠和超低延时领域的前沿话题，欢迎全校感兴趣的师生参加。&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;在线讲座时间：&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;2025年4月29日下午16:00-17:30&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;在线讲座信息：腾讯会议：&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;457-168-767&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;讲座题目：&lt;/font&gt;uRLLC for 5G and Beyond&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;讲座内容摘要：&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;The world is currently witnessing the rise of many mission critical applications such as tele-surgery, intelligent transportation, industry automation, virtual reality and augmented reality, vehicular communications, etc. Some of these applications will be enabled by the fifth-generation of cellular networks (5G), which will provide the required ultra-reliable low latency communication (URLLC).&amp;nbsp; However, guaranteeing these stringent reliability and end-to-end latency requirements continues to prove to be quite challenging, due to the significant shift in paradigms required in both theoretical fundamentals of wireless communications as well as design principles. In particular, a holistic framework that takes into account latency, reliability, availability, scalability, and decision-making under uncertainty is lacking. Addressing these challenges requires the development of new wireless technologies, underlying network protocols, and signal processing techniques. In this talk, we will present the key challenges and potential solutions for 5G and beyond 5G to support URLLC, in terms of error control coding improving reliability, channel access protocols for reducing latency, AI for meeting uRLLC requirements in different application scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;等线&quot;&gt;Yonghui Li教师简介：&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align:justify&quot;&gt;Yonghui Li is now a Professor and Director of Wireless Engineering Laboratory in School of Electrical and Information Engineering, University of Sydney. He is the recipient of the Australian Research Council (ARC)Queen Elizabeth II Fellowship in 2008 and ARC Future Fellowship in 2012. He is an IEEE Fellow and Clarivate highly cited researcher. His current research interests are in the area of wireless communications. Professor Li was an editor for IEEE transactions on communications, IEEE transactions on vehicular technology and guest editors for several special issues of IEEE journals, such as IEEE JSAC, IEEE IoT Journals, IEEE Communications Magazine. He received the best paper awards from several conferences. He has published one book, more than 300 papers in premier IEEE journals and more than 200 papers in premier IEEE conferences. His publications have been cited more than 25000 times.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
        </item>
